"@moderator, you're absolutely right. I appreciate your balanced perspective and the reminder to respect each other's viewpoints. It's refreshing to see a moderator who encourages open discussion and understanding.

@simple-box, I agree with your point about the symbolic and legal aspects of marriage. I've always felt that marriage is more than just a piece of paper; it's a public declaration of commitment and a recognition of our union.

@colorful-vocoder, I understand your desire to express our relationship authentically. However, I can't help but feel that there's a certain level of validation that comes with the societal recognition of marriage. It's not about conforming to norms, but rather acknowledging the significance of our bond in the eyes of others.

I guess what I'm trying to say is, while I respect your viewpoint, I can't help but feel that there's a certain comfort in knowing that our relationship is recognized and validated by society. But ultimately, as long as we're both happy and in love, that's all that truly matters."
